@c SQLtutor - Just Another Introduction to SQL

SQLtutor is a CGI script and a PostgreSQL database of SQL
tutorials, collections of SQL questions and answers.

Three environment variables SQLTUTOR_DATABASE, SQLTUTOR_WWW_USER
and SQLTUTOR_PASSWORD are defined in configure.ac and implicitly
are set to 'sqltutor' (Postgresql database name) and 'sqlquiz'
(www user for CGI script sqlutor) and 'sqlkrok' (password for
CGI skript). 

These variables are used by all makefiles and you can change
them if needed in the configure.ac file.


@section Building sqltutor

To build CGI script sqltutor run 

@example
   ./configue 
   make -C sqltutor
@end example

and copy sqltutor/sqltutor to your CGI directory.

For more information see the standard Basic Installation
instructions bellow.

@section Creating the database 

@examle
createdb SQLTUTOR_DATABASE

su -
su - postgres

createuser SQLTUTOR_WWW_USER

run psql and

ALTER USER SQLTUTOR_WWW_USER WITH PASSWORD 'xxx';
psql SQLTUTOR_DATABASE
CREATE LANGUAGE plpgsql;
@end example

@section Populating the databse

Change directory to 'database' and run 

@example
cd database
make install
@end example

Instructions for manual running of a script create-database.sh
are displayed.

@example
export SQLTUTOR_DATABASE=sqltutor
export SQLTUTOR_WWW_USER=sqlquiz
/bin/sh create-database.sh
@end example

@section Populate tutorials and datasets

Run in any order from the project home directory

@example
make -C tutorials install
make -C datasets  install
@end example

If old tutorials and/or datasets have been installed, run

@example
make -C tutorials clean install
make -C datasets  clean install
@end example



